e|[[Hakan Ko\u00e7]]|TUR|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 10\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Saeid Ebrahimi]]|IRI|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 11\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Saleh Emara]]|EGY|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 12\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Nicolae Ceban]]|MDA|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 13\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Stefan Kehrer]]|GER|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 14\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[David Zilberman (wrestler)|David Zilberman]]|CAN|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 15\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Luis Vivenes]]|VEN|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 16\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Aleksey Krupnyakov]]|KGZ|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 17\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Mateusz Gucman]]|POL|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 18\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Vincent Aka-Akesse]]|FRA|2008 Summer}}\n|-\n| 19\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Daniel Cormier]]|USA|2008 Summer}}\n|}\n\n* [[Taimuraz Tigiyev]] of [[Kazakhstan]] originally finished second, but in November 2016, it was announced that he tested positive dopint-test.<ref>{{cite web|title=IOC sanctions nine athletes for failing anti-doping test at Beijing 2008|url=https://www.olympic.org/news/ioc-sanctions-nine-athletes-for-failing-anti-doping-test-at-beijing-2008|publisher=[[IOC]]|accessdate=26 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe medals were reawarded by FILA following this decision<ref>{{cite web|title=IOC Sanctions Wrestlers for Anti-Doping Violations at Beijing 2008 and London 2012|url=https://unitedworldwrestling.org/article/todo%20|publisher=[[United World Wrestling|FILA]]|accessdate=22 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wrestling at the 2008 Summer Olympics - Men's freestyle 96 kg}}\n[[Category:Wrestling at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's freestyle 96 kg\n|games = 2008 Summer \n|image = \n|caption =\n|venue = [[China Agricultural University Gymnasium]]\n|date = 21 August\n|competitors = 19\n|nations = 19\n|gold        = [[Shirvani Muradov]]\n|goldNOC     = RUS\n|silver      = [[Giorgi Gogshelidze]]\n|silverNOC   = GEO\n|bronze      = [[Khetag Gazyumov]]\n|bronzeNOC   = AZE\n|bronze2     = [[Michel Batista (wrestler)|Michel Batista]]\n|bronzeNOC2  = CUB\n|prev = [[Wrestling at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 96 kg|2004]]\n|next = [[Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 96 kg|2012]]\n}}\n\n{{WrestlingAt2008SummerOlympics}}\n'''Men's freestyle 96&nbsp;kg''' competition at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], [[China]], took place on 21 August at the [[China Agricultural University Gymnasium]].\n\nThis [[freestyle wrestling]] competition consists of a single-elimination tournament, with a [[repechage]] used to determine the winner of two bronze medals. The two finalists face off for gold and silver medals. Each wrestler who loses to one of the two finalists moves into the repechage, culminating in a pair of bronze medal matches featuring the semifinal losers each facing the remaining repechage opponent from their half of the bracket.\n\nEach bout consists of up to three rounds, lasting two minutes apiece. The wrestler who scores more points in each round is the winner of that rounds; the bout ends when one wrestler has won two rounds (and thus the match).\n\n==Schedule==\n<small>All times are [[China Standard Time]] ([[UTC+08:00]])</small>\n{|class = \"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=150|Date\n! width=100|Time\n! width=150|Event\n|-\n| rowspan=3| 21 August 2008 || 09:30\u201313:00 || Qualification rounds\n|-\n| 16:00\u201317:00 || Repechage\n|-\n| 17:00\u201319:45 || bgcolor=ffffcc|Finals\n|}\n\n==Results==\n;Legend\n*'''F''' \u2014 Won by [[Pin (amateur wrestling)|fall]]\n*'''W''' \u2014 Won by walkover\n\n===Final===\n\n{{2TeamBracket-Tennis3\n| seeds = no\n| RD1=Final\n| nowrap = no\n\n| team-width=205\n| score-width=15\n\n| RD1-team1={{flagIOCathlete|[[Taimuraz Tigiyev]]|KAZ|2008 Summer}}\n| RD1-score1-1=0\n| RD1-score1-