web.archive.org/web/20110719205923/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms30.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=19 July 2011|title=30th Annual Young Artist Awards - Nominations / Special Awards|date=19 July 2011|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| 2010\n| [[31st Young Artist Awards]]\n| {{won}}\n| <center><ref name=aaa/></center>\n|-\n| 2011\n| [[32nd Young Artist Awards]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <center><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808150433/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=8 August 2013|title=32nd Annual Young Artist Awards - Nominations / Special Awards|date=8 August 2013|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref></center>\n|-\n| 2013\n| [[34th Young Artist Awards]]\n| [[Young Artist Award for Best Leading Young Actress in a Feature Film|Best Performance in a Feature Film - Leading Young Actress]]\n| ''[[Paranormal Activity 4]]''\n| {{won}}\n| <center><ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 3\"/></center>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|1105980}}\n* {{Instagram|kathrynnewton}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Newton, Kathryn}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American soap opera actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Orlando, Florida]]\n[[Category:Notre Dame High School (Sherman Oaks, California) alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date = April 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date = April 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kathryn Newton\n| image              = Kathryn Newton (2012).png\n| caption            = Newton in October 2012\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1997|02|08|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Orlando]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actress\n| imagesize          = \n| birth_name         = Kathryn Love Newton\n| yearsactive        = 2002\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Kathryn Love Newton''' (born February 8, 1997)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thenetline.com/people/kathryn-newton/|title=Kathryn Newton Biography|website=TheNetline.com|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref> is an American [[actress]], best known for her role as Allie Pressman in the [[Netflix]] TV series ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]'', Abigail Carlson in ''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]'' and Louise Brooks in the [[CBS]] [[television series]] ''[[Gary Unmarried]]''. Newton also stars in the 2012 film ''[[Paranormal Activity 4]]'' as Alex Nelson, which earned her the [[34th Young Artist Awards|2013]] [[Young Artist Award]] for [[Young Artist Award for Best Leading Young Actress in a Feature Film|Best Leading Young Actress in a Feature Film]]<ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html|title=34th Annual Young Artist Awards|website=[[Young Artist Award]]s.org|accessdate=2013-03-31|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511130613/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html|archivedate=2013-05-11}}</ref> and the 2019 film ''[[Detective Pikachu (film)|Pok\u00e9mon Detective Pikachu]]'' as Lucy Stevens, alongside [[Justice Smith]]. She is also known for portraying the older version of [[Claire Novak]] in the CW series ''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]'' and for her role as the older Joanie Clark in the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] television series ''[[Halt and Catch Fire (TV series)|Halt and Catch Fire]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usga.org/articles/2012/05/teen-actress-newton-hopes-to-star-in-womens-open-21474846724.html|title=Teen Actress Newton Hopes To Star In Women's Open|publisher=|accessdate=18 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170914035321/http://www.usga.org/articles/2012/05/teen-actress-newton-hopes-to-star-in-womens-open-21474846724.html|archivedate=14 September 2017|df=}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nNewton was born in Orlando, Florida,{{cn|date=January 2020}} and is the only child of Robin and David Newton.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.usga.org/articles/2012/05/teen-actress-newton-hopes-to-star-in-womens-open-21474846724.html|title=After appearing in \"Gary Unmarried,\" \"Bad Teacher,\" 15-year-old seeks role on golf's biggest stage|last=Shefter|first=David|date=1 May 2012|website=United States Golf Association|access-date=29 May 2019}}</ref> She started her career at age four, making her television debut on the [[soap opera]] ''[[All My Children]]'',<ref name=\"USGA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usga.org/articles/2012/05/teen-actress-newton-hopes-to-star-in-womens-open-21474846724.html|title=After appearing in \"Gary Unmarried,\" \"Bad Teacher,\" 15-year-old seeks role on golf's biggest stage|date=May 1, 2012|work=[[United States Golf Association|USGA]]|accessdate=February 11, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216090642/http://www.usga.org/articles/2012/05/teen-actress-newton-hopes-to-star-in-womens-open-21474846724.html|archivedate=February 16, 2016|df=}}</ref> playing [[Colby Marian Chandler]] from 2001 to 2004. Meanwhile, she also starred in two [[short films]], ''Abbie Down East'' (2002) and ''Bun-Bun'' (2003).<ref name=\"USGA\" />  In 2008 Newton was cast in the role of Louise Brooks in the [[CBS]] [[television series]] ''[[Gary Unmarried]]''. When she was twelve, her family moved to Los Angeles,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/kathryn-newton-big-little-lies-vogue-june-2018-issue|title=Big Little Lies Star Kathryn Newton Is Taking Over Screens Big and Small|website=Vogue|date=18 May 2018}}</ref> where she attended the [[Notre Dame High School (Sherman Oaks, California)|Notre Dame High School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/best-golfer-in-hollywood-kathryn-newton|title=The Best Golfer in Hollywood: Kathryn Newton can light it up on screen or on the course|website=Golf Digest|date=17 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Newton won two [[Young Artist Awards]] for \"Best Performance in a TV Comedy Series\" and \"Best Performance in a TV series (Comedy or Drama)\" for [[Gary Unmarried]].<ref name=aaa>{{Cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms31.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20160304033113/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms31.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2016-03-04|title=31st Annual Young Artist Awards - 2010 |website=www.youngartistawards.org |access-date=2016-06-14}}</ref>{{cbignore}} Newton played the role of Chase Rubin-Rossi in the 2011 film ''[[Bad Teacher]]'' alongside [[Cameron Diaz]].<ref name=\"Crave\">{{cite news|url=http://www.craveonline.com/site/198303-i-felt-invincible-kathryn-newton-on-paranormal-activity-4|title=I Felt Invincible: Kathryn Newton on Paranormal Activity 4|date=October 19, 2012|work=[[CraveOnline]]|accessdate=February 11, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216101947/http://www.craveonline.com/site/198303-i-felt-invincible-kathryn-newton-on-paranormal-activity-4|archivedate=February 16, 2016|df=}}</ref>  She had the lead role, Alex, in the 2012 film ''[[Paranormal Activity 4]]'', the fourth in the [[Paranormal Activity (film series)|franchise]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/story/2012-08-31/horror-films-dominate-fall-film-calendar/57456870/1|title=It's scream season already as scary movies crowd calendar|date=August 31, 2012|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=September 3, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903004421/http://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/story/2012-08-31/horror-films-dominate-fall-film-calendar/57456870/1|archivedate=September 3, 2012|df=}}</ref> and won an award at the [[34th Young Artist Awards]] for her performance in the film.<ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 3\"/> Beginning in [[Supernatural (season 10)|season 10]], she had a recurring role as Claire Novak on ''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]''. In 2017, Newton appeared in the HBO series ''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]'' based on the [[Liane Moriarty]] novel of the [[Big Little Lies (novel)|same name]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/hbo-big-little-lies-cast-alexander-skarsgard-james-tupper-1201672747/|title=Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd and James Tupper Join HBO's 'Big Little Little Lies'|date=January 5, 2016|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=February 11, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216044607/http://variety.com/2016/tv/news/hbo-big-little-lies-cast-alexander-skarsgard-james-tupper-1201672747/|archivedate=February 16, 2016|df=}}</ref> She also had major roles in the films ''[[Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri]]'' and ''[[Ben Is Back]]''. In both unrelated films, she played the sister of [[Lucas Hedges]]' character.\n\nNewton had the female lead in the 2019 blockbuster ''[[Detective Pikachu (film)|Pok\u00e9mon Detective Pikachu]]'', a live action film based on the [[Detective Pikachu (video game)|video game of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/big-little-lies-kathryn-newton-legendarys-pokemon-pic-1202626091/|title='Big Little Lies' Actress Kathryn Newton to Star in Live-Action Pokemon Movie|last=Kroll|first=Justin|website=Variety|date=November 29, 2017|accessdate=November 29, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130003530/http://variety.com/2017/film/news/big-little-lies-kathryn-newton-legendarys-pokemon-pic-1202626091/|archivedate=November 30, 2017}}</ref> She also plays the lead role of Allie in the [[Netflix]] mystery drama series ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]'', which premiered on May 10, 2019. She will next star in an [[Untitled Christopher Landon project|untitled thriller]] film opposite [[Vince Vaughn]], directed by [[Christopher Landon (filmmaker)|Christopher Landon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/vince-vaughn-kathryn-newton-chris-landon-body-swapping-blumhouse-thriller-1202707450/|title=Vince Vaughn, Kathryn Newton Topline Chris Landon Body-Swapping Blumhouse Thriller|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=August 29, 2019|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref> and in ''[[The Map of Tiny Perfect Things]]'' directed by Ian Samuels.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/map-of-tiny-perfect-things-amazon-studios-akiva-goldsman-filmnation-1203502837/|title=Amazon Studios Boards \u2018Map of Tiny Perfect Things\u2019 From Akiva Goldsman and FilmNation (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Matt|last=Donnelly|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nNewton has been golfing since she was a child. She began playing tournaments at age 8.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/best-golfer-in-hollywood-kathryn-newton|title=Think Young, Play Hard: Kathryn Newton|last=Jr|first=Ron Kaspriske,Walter Iooss|website=Golf Digest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> \n\nNewton graduated from [[Notre Dame High School (Sherman Oaks, California)|Notre Dame High School]] in 2015. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kathrynnewton/status/605434251962507265|title=The moment b4 I really graduated. #imadeit #classof2015pic.twitter.com/tdfqIutz3e|last=NEWTON|first=KATHRYN|date=2015-06-01|website=@kathrynnewton|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kathrynnewton.net/|title=Starring Kathryn Newton {{!}} kathrynnewton.net|date=2018-10-12|website=Starring Kathryn Newton|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> She was a member of the [[Notre Dame High School (Sherman Oaks, California)|Notre Dame High School]] womens golf team<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailynews.com/sports/20130905/high-school-roundup-record-setting-round-for-kathryn-newton-notre-dame-girls-golf-team|title=HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP: Record-setting round for Kathryn Newton, Notre Dame girls golf team|date=2013-09-05|website=Daily News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailynews.com/sports/20131010/roundup-katelyn-reynolds-kathryn-newton-lead-notre-dame-girls-golf-team-past-harvard-westlake|title=Roundup: Katelyn Reynolds, Kathryn Newton lead Notre Dame girls golf team past Harvard-Westlake|date=2013-10-10|website=Daily News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> \n\nShe postponed college to pursue her acting career.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/best-golfer-in-hollywood-kathryn-newton|title=Think Young, Play Hard: Kathryn Newton|last=Jr|first=Ron Kaspriske,Walter Iooss|website=Golf Digest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref> She considered playing as a 'walk-on' member of [[University of Southern California]] womens golf team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marieclaire.com/celebrity/news/a25459/kathryn-newton-interview-big-little-lies/|title=The Surprising Perk of Playing Reese Witherspoon's Daughter on TV|last=Bonner|first=Mehera|date=2017-02-21|website=Marie Claire|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.golfdigest.com/story/best-golfer-in-hollywood-kathryn-newton|title=Think Young, Play Hard: Kathryn Newton|last=Jr|first=Ron Kaspriske,Walter Iooss|website=Golf Digest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\nNewton has 3 [[Poodle]] dogs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://schonmagazine.com/schon-36-kathryn-newton/|title=Sch\u00f6n! 36 {{!}} kathryn newton|website=Sch\u00f6n! Magazine|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Note\n|-\n| 2002\n| scope=\"row\" 